      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BENNIE AND THE JETS NZ (10) has had eight weeks off since breaking last start but has trialled nicely twice in that time. Had recorded three wins and a Bendigo Cup placing from his previous four starts. With his A-game he is good enough to overcome the back row draw. IRON WOMEN (7) resumes after tackling the good fillies last season, winning a Vicbred Super Series heat here two back. Owns a good record at this distance and should be ready to go off a trial placing. NO MONEY NO HONEY (5) broke when last seen in the G3 Holmfield in August but kicked off that campaign with a Bendigo win so can perform well when fresh. CALL ME JACK (4) has trialled well since the fresh effort and draws well so can  progress.",
